The project consists of a simple Registration Form webpage, allowing users to input their information. 
The HTML and CSS files work together to create a visually appealing and user-friendly form.

Learnings and Studies

HTML:
  Utilized various input types (text, email, password, file, number, checkbox, radio, select) for form elements.
  Explored the use of labels and fieldsets for better form structure.
  Employed the required attribute for mandatory form fields.

CSS:
  Implemented responsive design with percentage and viewport units.
  Used flexbox for layout and positioning of form elements.
  Styled form elements for a cohesive and visually appealing design.
  Employed media queries to adjust styling for different screen sizes.

Best Practices:
  Followed best practices for code readability and maintainability.
  Ensured a mobile-first approach by using responsive units and flexible layouts.

Accessibility:
Ensured a logical tab order for keyboard navigation.
Utilized semantic HTML elements for better accessibility.
